cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with inferring depth from an RGB image using a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) and explores variants of the proposed approach in an ablative study. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the proposed approach can be used as an input to several other hand analysis and perception algorithms that require depth input, which is relevant to robotics. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely as the paper proposes a novel approach to a computer vision problem using a CNN. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper uses a stacked hourglass model as its main building block and employs intermediate supervision in several outputs of the proposed architecture in a staged approach. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is also possible as the paper deals with 3D reconstruction of hands based on RGB information, which is relevant to graphics.
